        "user": "Here is the canonical definition of \"gradient descent\": Gradient descent is a first-order iterative optimization algorithm that minimizes a differentiable function by repeatedly stepping in the direction of the negative gradient at the current point, with step size controlled by a learning rate. Acknowledge that you have read it.",
